Chile Stocks: Cap, Empresas La Polar, Empresas Hites, Provida

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-07-14T20:50:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/chile-stocks-cap-empresas-la-polar-empresas-hites-provida.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:22 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.6 percent to 4,698.15.  Adm. de Fondos de Pensiones Provida SA (PROVIDA CC), a unit
of  Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA, rose 2.5 percent
to 2,222.4 pesos, the biggest gain in a week.  Chile ’s largest
pension fund manager rose today after saying that rumors
surrounding its investments in retailer  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)  are
“unfounded.” The stock slumped 7.7 percent yesterday after
website Panorama News reported that a BBVA unit used funds
managed by Provida to cover an irrecoverable loan it made to La
Polar.  Cap SA (CAP)   fell 1.6 percent to 22,098 pesos, its fifth
day of losses. Chile’s largest steel producer and iron miner
fell in line with lower base metal prices.  Empresas Hites SA (HITES)   fell 0.9 percent to 555 pesos.
The department store operator had its 12-month price estimate
cut to 650 pesos from 825 pesos at Banchile-Citi, the joint
research department of local lender Banco de Chile and Citigroup
Inc., which also reiterated a “hold” rating, according to a
note to clients dated yesterday.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR CC) fell 0.4 percent to
554.43 pesos, its fourth day of losses. Chile’s securities
regulator said it will charge former and current executives of
the retailer for providing false information and for  insider
trading .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
